    "Body": " Audio Visual (AV) / Cyber Operations Specialist Spectrum Comm Inc - 4.0 Hurlburt Field, FL Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $61,000 - $88,000 a year Qualifications LAN IAT Level II CCNA Security Microsoft Powerpoint CompTIA Security+ Full Job Description Spectrum is seeking an Audio Visual (AV) / Cyber Operations Specialist to support the U. S. Air Force Special Operations Command (AFSOC) and U. S. Air Force Special Operations School (USAFSOS) at Hurlburt Field, FL. Job Responsibilities: Operate and maintain Information Technology (IT), possess a working knowledge and experience in cyber operations and be able to operate classified and unclassified multimedia, VTC associated software, hardware, and presentation systems in auditoriums, classrooms, and conference room in order for USAFSOS to carry out its mission. Provide still and video documentation of events of informational or historical value as determined by the COR. Provide presentation services on a routine basis for two (2) conference rooms, two (2) auditoriums, and three (3) classrooms. Presentation equipment consists of, but is not limited to, overhead projectors, 35mm slide projectors, 16mm motion picture film projectors, video projectors, 1/2 inch and 3/4 inch video cassette players/recorders, video/audio teleconferencing equipment, audio reel-to-reel decks, audio cassette decks, microphones, video monitors, and associated computer equipment. Presentations range from a single projector to multimedia requirements. Ensure preparation, calibration, and functional operation of all visual information equipment for presentations prior to the start of briefings, meetings, and instructional sessions. Assist briefers with presentations to include monitoring presentations, recording speakers, mixing/editing recordings, and providing advice on proper briefing format for optimal performance on available equipment. Manage access to all audiovisual equipment. This includes establishing procedures for access to equipment in the projection booths and equipment in the classrooms and conference rooms. Serve as the focal point for modifications, improvements, and integration of audiovisual equipment in support of presentations. Oversee improvements and acknowledge the acceptance of these improvements to ensure all equipment effected is operational and functional. Serve as the focal point for all classified equipment used for audiovisual operations. Further, configure and manage all hard drives (classified and unclassified) used for audiovisual support. Also, be responsible for any classroom computer system(s) used to support school requirements. This includes any mini-Local Area Network used in the school. Coordinate upgrades of software and equipment to meet multimedia presentation requirements and comply with related Air Force Instructions for emissions security. Conduct system administrator duties on all audiovisual computer equipment as necessary and coordinate with the unit computer manager to ensure compliance with applicable regulations. Provide computer hardware and software configuration management for all audiovisual computers in coordination with the USAFSOS senior communications officer. Provide formal and informal training to guest lecturers/briefers on the operation of audiovisual equipment at the request of COR. Training shall be used to familiarize personnel with visual information equipment on-hand, procedures for presentations, and limitations of the equipment. As needed, provide technical support for reformatting briefings. Develop and provide training to instructors/speakers on methods for preparing briefings/instructional presentations. This training shall include equipment familiarization, audiovisual capabilities, and presentation management procedures. Training shall be provided upon initial assignment to the organization. Refresher training, which shall include an emphasis on new or infrequently used capabilities of presentation software and hardware, shall be provided on a quarterly basis, or as required in support of presentations. This training may be provided by both formal hands-on and through Advanced Distributed Learning delivery. Conduct Video Teleconferencing (VTC) of courses to multiple locations. This effort may include market research for sources of equipment and supplies, evaluate equipment, and provide advice in the selection of equipment to improve the current configuration and ensure integration with existing equipment. Provide total management of all VTC facilities, scheduling, administration requirements in getting briefings to the distance end, and provide all training to all users, both faculty and management, both on-site and at remote locations. Develop and manage an equipment buy/replacement plan on an annual basis. Be responsible for the operation and minor maintenance of VTC equipment to support USAFSOS courses, Off-Site Courses (OSCs), Off-Site Tutorials (OSTs), and other events. This shall include management of secure and non-secure operations of VTC equipment and crypto equipment required during secure mode operations. Track the usage of the VTC system on a monthly basis IAW the COR s format. Function as the alternate crypto custodian and will be responsible for the daily operation of all assigned crypto equipment and material. Required Skills and Experience: Secret security clearance. Possesses a working knowledge and experience in cyber operations. Experience in operating classified and unclassified multimedia, VTC associated software, hardware, and presentation systems in auditoriums, classrooms, and conference rooms. Knowledgeable in the following types of capture devices: scanners, computers, video, and still camera. Storage devices include hard drives, removable cartridge discs, tapes, 3. 5 inch floppy disks and CD ROM and DVD. Some of the items transferred or captured on digital media include, but are not limited to photographs, hard copies, video, and original multimedia documentation. Demonstrated proficiency in the use of the Internet for briefing purposes. Must be skilled at access, use, and download of products from the worldwide web. This includes being able to configure local computers to receive real time briefings broadcast over the Internet. High level of expertise in video, multimedia, and personal computers. High level of familiarity with use of the Internet, basic telecommunications technologies, maintenance and alignment of audiovisual equipment, and video teleconferencing. Proficiency in multimedia technology. Extensive knowledge and experience on Windows, Word, and PowerPoint software. Must have one of the following Information Assurance Technician (IAT) Level II certifications: CCNA Security CySA+ GICSP GSEC Security+ CE SSCP Spectrum is proud of our diverse workforce and diligently committed to remaining an Equal Opportunity Employer. Spectrum governs all employment-related decisions without regard to an individual's race, color, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, religion, national origin, age, disability, veteran status or any other protected classification. [Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer \u2013 minorities/females/veterans/individuals with disabilities/sexual orientation/gender identity] ", 
